    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>'Instant Runoff' Voting</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Daniel Gonneau letter comments on John B Anderson's July 5 Op-Ed, endorsing idea of 'instant runoff' in presidential elections</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>John B. Anderson (Op-Ed, July 5) is correct that ''instant runoff'' voting would help to solve the worst problem with our two-party system: the silencing of third-party and other non-mainstream issues and voters. Allowing voters to select first-, second-  and third-choice candidates would eliminate the profoundly undemocratic process of deciding whether to ''waste'' a vote on a third-party candidate.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>John B. Anderson (Op-Ed, July 5) is correct that ''instant runoff'' voting would help to solve the worst problem with our two-party system: the silencing of third-party and other non-mainstream issues and voters. Allowing voters to select first-, second-  and third-choice candidates would eliminate the profoundly undemocratic process of deciding whether to ''waste'' a vote on a third-party candidate.</p>
        <p>Shouldn't the world's most advanced democracy also have the world's most advanced electoral process?</p>
        <p>DANIEL GONNEAU  Astoria, Queens, July 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
